1. Cross Entropy Loss ¶Consider a super simple neural network: a super simple neural networksimple_nn "a super simple neural network The forward propogation process of the network would be: $$\hat{z_1}= eta_1x$$ $$\hat{z_2}= eta_2x$$ $$Softmax(\hat{z_i}),\ i\in{2}$$ Consider a cross entropy loss: $$J( eta)=-p\log(q)-(1-p)\log(1-q)$$ $$=-p\log( rac{e^{ eta_1x}}{e^{ eta_1x}+e^{ eta_2x}})-(1-p)\log( rac{e^{ eta_2x}}{e^{ eta_1x}+e^{ eta_2x}})$$ $$=…$$ $$=-p\log{e^{ eta_1x}}-(1-p)log{e^{ eta_2x}}+log(e^{ eta_1x}+e^{ eta_2x})$$ $$=-p eta_1x-(1-p) eta_2x+log(e^{ eta_1x}+e^{ eta_2x})$$ where $p$ denotes the true label of $z_1$ and $1-p$ denotes the true label of $z_2$, $ eta_1$ and $ eta_2$ are model parameters, $x$ denotes the model input and is a scalar. So then, the cross entropy loss could be visualized as: var myChart = echarts.init(document.getElementById('echarts400'));var option = eval('('+"
{
